720304f-a.title: Manhattan: Hamilton Place - 143rd Street (West)
720304f-a.text:
134-142 Hamilton Place, at the N.W. corner of West 143rd Street,
showing a 6-story apartment house; the Chilmark Hall. At this point
the old Bloomingdale Road turned, to continue eastward to, and end at
Eingsbridge Road, after following the present Hamilton Place line.
October 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

721675f-a.title: Manhattan: Hamilton Street - 143rd Street (West)
721675f-a.text:
(1)
Monroe Street, west from and including Market Street. Also shown
is Market Street, west side, north from Hamilton, to and including Momoe
Streets.
September 7, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
NO PEPRODUCTIOIIS.
(2)
Another view, showing a view westward on Bamilton (left) Street. Minaretsf
shown on the right are atop P.5. No. 177, at the S.E. corner of Market and
Monroe Streets.
June 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
